  # Why: NATS exactly-once delivery guarantees each brief is processed by one runner
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Two simultaneous briefs are each delivered to exactly one runner
    Given two guardkit_vs_vanilla briefs are published to NATS within the same second
    When both briefs are consumed from the work queue
    Then each brief should be processed by exactly one runner instance
    And no brief should be processed more than once

  # Why: NATS reconnection during eval should not abort in-progress arms
  @edge-case
  Scenario: NATS disconnection during arm execution does not abort the arm
    Given the GuardKit arm is executing
    And the NATS connection is temporarily lost
